{"type":"text","timestamp":1775846683317,"sessionID":"ses_2874c73b5ffeTv2w8vyLSfAs6g","part":{"id":"prt_d78b4c4f3001LvYSgMakzsIeQC","messageID":"msg_d78b49fc7001R9Kn5Cz15fRCws","sessionID":"ses_2874c73b5ffeTv2w8vyLSfAs6g","type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me write the design.md file:","time":{"start":1775846683311,"end":1775846683311}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846683411,"sessionID":"ses_2874c73b5ffeTv2w8vyLSfAs6g","part":{"id":"prt_d78b5f2b3001ZDKHsAiEjtQE1i","messageID":"msg_d78b49fc7001R9Kn5Cz15fRCws","sessionID":"ses_2874c73b5ffeTv2w8vyLSfAs6g","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-e9cc50c9d1854507b236ec579b1f7071","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md","content":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe WorkloadManager package provides the HTTP service framework for managing AgentCube sandbox lifecycles on Kubernetes. It orchestrates sandbox creation, deletion, garbage collection, and health monitoring through a layered architecture combining Kubernetes dynamic client operations with an in-memory store for session tracking.\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          HTTPServer                                  │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │   Router    │  │ Middleware   │  │         Handlers            │ │\n│  │  (chi/v5)   │  │ Recovery     │  │ DeletionHandler             │ │\n│  │             │  │ Logging      │  │ HealthHandler               │ │\n│  │             │  │ CORS         │  │ HandlerFuncAdapter          │ │\n│  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                               │                                      │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                    SandboxLifecycleManager                       │ │\n│  │  - DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                                 │ │\n│  │  - ForceDeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                            │ │\n│  │  - IsExpired(sandbox)                                            │ │\n│  │  - IsIdleExpired(sandbox, timeout)                               │ │\n│  │  - GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                                    │ │\n│  │  - UpdateSandboxStatus(ctx, sessionID, status)                  │ │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                               │                                      │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────┐│\n│  │ GarbageCollector │  │   K8sClient  │  │       MemoryStore       ││\n│  │ - runLoop()      │  │ dynamicClient│  │ - StoreSandbox()        ││\n│  │ - runOnce()      │  │ coreClient   │  │ - GetSandboxBySessionID ││\n│  │ - Start/Stop     │  │ podLister    │  │ - UpdateSandbox()       ││\n│  │                  │  │ informerFact │  │ - DeleteSandboxBySession││\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────┘  │ - ListExpiredSandboxes  ││\n│                        ┌──────────────┐  │ - ListInactiveSandboxes ││\n│                        │  Informers   │  └─────────────────────────┘│\n│                        │ factory      │                              │\n│                        │ Start/Wait   │                              │\n│                        └──────────────┘                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Component Responsibilities:**\n\n| Component | Responsibility |\n|-----------|---------------|\n| `HTTPServer` | HTTP lifecycle management, graceful shutdown, handler registration |\n| `Router` | Chi router wrapper for route registration |\n| `Middleware` | Recovery, logging, CORS handling for all requests |\n| `Handlers` | HTTP endpoint implementation for sandbox operations |\n| `SandboxLifecycleManager` | Core sandbox lifecycle orchestration (create/delete/status) |\n| `GarbageCollector` | Background cleanup of expired/idle sandboxes |\n| `K8sClient` | Kubernetes client wrapper with dynamic/client-go/informers |\n| `Informers` | SharedInformerFactory for pod watching |\n| `MemoryStore` | In-memory session tracking with expiration indices |\n| `ClientCache` | Token-scoped dynamic client caching for multi-tenant access |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP routing |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Dynamic client for CRD operations |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/informers` | SharedInformerFactory for caching |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | K8s API error handling |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller utilities |\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Core Types\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind               string              // AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter/Sandbox/SandboxClaim\n    SandboxID          string              // Unique sandbox identifier\n    SandboxNamespace   string              // K8s namespace\n    SandboxName        string              // K8s resource name\n    Name               string              // Runtime name\n    SessionID          string              // Session identifier (primary key)\n    CreatedAt          time.Time           // Creation timestamp\n    ExpiresAt          time.Time           // Expiration timestamp\n    Status             string              // Current status\n    EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint // Network entry points\n    UserToken          string              // User authentication token\n    ServiceAccount     string              // K8s service account\n    ServiceAccountName string              // Service account name\n    LastActivity       time.Time           // Last activity timestamp\n}\n```\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\ntype ValidationError struct {\n    Field  string\n    Reason string\n}\n\ntype NotFoundError struct {\n    Resource string\n    Name     string\n}\n\ntype InternalError struct {\n    Err error\n}\n\ntype ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n    Dependency string\n}\n\ntype ConflictError struct {\n    Resource string\n    Err      error\n}\n```\n\n### Configuration Types\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Addr            string        // \":8080\"\n    ReadTimeout     time.Duration // 15s\n    WriteTimeout    time.Duration // 15s\n    IdleTimeout     time.Duration // 60s\n    ShutdownTimeout time.Duration // 30s\n    EnableHealthz   bool\n    EnableReadyz    bool\n}\n\ntype LifecycleConfig struct {\n    DefaultTTL          time.Duration // 8h\n    DefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration // 15m\n    DefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration // 8h\n    GCInterval          time.Duration // 2m\n    GCOnceTimeout       time.Duration // 2m\n    DeletionGracePeriod int64         // 0\n    DeletionTimeout     time.Duration // 30s\n}\n```\n\n### Constants and GVR\n\n```go\nconst (\n    DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n    DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n    DefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour\n    SandboxCreationTimeout    = 2 * time.Minute\n    SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second\n    InformerSyncTimeout       = 1 * time.Minute\n    GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute\n    GCBatchSize               = 16\n)\n\nvar SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n    Group:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n    Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n    Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n}\n\nvar SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n    Group:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n    Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n    Resource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n}\n```\n\n### Labels and Annotations\n\n```go\nconst (\n    LabelKeySessionID    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n    LabelKeyWorkloadName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n    LabelKeySandboxName  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n    LabelKeyManagedBy    = \"managed-by\"\n    ManagedByValue       = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"\n    \n    AnnotationKeyIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n    AnnotationKeyPodName     = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n)\n```\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### Sandbox Deletion\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId}` | Delete AgentRuntime sandbox |\n| DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId}` | Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n\n**Request:**\n- `sessionId` (path parameter) - Required\n- `force` (optional) - Force deletion with gracePeriod=0\n- `gracePeriodSeconds` (optional) - Deletion grace period\n\n**Response (200):**\n```json\n{\n    \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n    \"status\": \"deleted\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response (404):**\n```json\n{\n    \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n    \"status\": \"not_found\",\n    \"message\": \"not found: sandbox/session-123\"\n}\n```\n\n### Health Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/healthz` | Basic health check |\n| GET | `/readyz` | Readiness check (informers sync) |\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Classification\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Code |\n|------------|-------------|------|\n| `ValidationError` | 400 | VALIDATION_ERROR |\n| `NotFoundError` | 404 | NOT_FOUND |\n| `ServiceUnavailableError` | 503 | SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE |\n| `ConflictError` | 409 | (via K8s API) |\n| `InternalError` | 500 | INTERNAL_ERROR |\n\n### HandleError Function\n\n```go\nfunc HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, _ *http.Request, err error) {\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n    \n    var resp ErrorResponse\n    var status int\n    \n    switch e := err.(type) {\n    case *ValidationError:\n        status = http.StatusBadRequest\n        resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", Message: \"Invalid request parameter\", ...}\n    case *NotFoundError:\n        status = http.StatusNotFound\n        resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"NOT_FOUND\", Message: e.Error()}\n    case *ServiceUnavailableError:\n        status = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n        resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\", ...}\n    case *InternalError:\n        status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n        resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", Message: \"Unexpected server error\"}\n    default:\n        status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n        resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", Message: \"Unexpected server error\"}\n    }\n    \n    w.WriteHeader(status)\n    json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n}\n```\n\n### K8s API Error Handling\n\n```go\nfunc handleDeleteError(err error) error {\n    if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        return nil  // Already deleted, success\n    }\n    if apierrors.IsConflict(err) {\n        return &ConflictError{Resource: \"sandbox\", Err: err}\n    }\n    return &InternalError{Err: err}\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Patterns\n\n1. **Unit Tests** - Each component tested independently with mocks\n2. **Fake K8s Clients** - `dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient`, `fake.NewSimpleClientset`\n3. **Mock Logger** - Simple struct capturing Info/Error calls\n4. **Test Informer Factory** - `NewTestInformerFactory` for controlled sync\n\n### Test Helpers\n\n```go\ntype mockLogger struct {\n    infoCalls  []string\n    errorCalls []string\n}\n\nfunc (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {\n    l.infoCalls = append(l.infoCalls, msg)\n}\n\nfunc (l *mockLogger) Error(msg string, args ...any) {\n    l.errorCalls = append(l.errorCalls, msg)\n}\n\nfunc NewTestInformerFactory(client kubernetes.Interface) informers.SharedInformerFactory {\n    return informers.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, time.Minute)\n}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Areas\n\n| File | Test Coverage |\n|------|---------------|\n| `lifecycle_test.go` | DeleteSandbox, ForceDeleteSandbox, IsExpired, IsIdleExpired, GetSandbox, UpdateSandboxStatus |\n| `k8s_client_test.go` | NewK8sClient, StartInformers, WaitForCacheSync, PodLister, ClientCache |\n| `store_test.go` | StoreSandbox, GetSandboxBySessionID, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandbox, ListExpired/Inactive |\n| `garbage_collector_test.go` | runOnce, Start/Stop, idle timeout behavior |\n| `handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go` | HTTP deletion endpoints, error handling |\n| `server_test.go` | Start/Stop, GracefulShutdown, handler registration |\n\n### Integration Test Strategy\n\n```go\nfunc TestIntegration_ServerLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n    fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n    informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n    \n    k8sClient := &K8sClient{\n        dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n        coreClient:      fakeClient,\n        informerFactory: informerFactory,\n    }\n    \n    store := NewMemoryStore()\n    logger := &mockLogger{}\n    cfg := DefaultConfig()\n    \n    server := NewHTTPServerWithClients(cfg, logger, k8sClient, store)\n    \n    // Register handlers, start server, verify endpoints\n}\n```\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [x] HTTPServer graceful shutdown with context timeout\n- [x] K8sClient with dynamic/client-go/informers integration\n- [x] MemoryStore with expiration and activity indices\n- [x] GarbageCollector background cleanup loop\n- [x] SandboxLifecycleManager handles Sandbox + SandboxClaim deletion\n- [x] Error classification with structured JSON responses\n- [x] DeletionReason enum for tracking cleanup triggers\n- [x] ClientCache for multi-tenant token-scoped clients\n- [x] Chi router with middleware chain (Recovery → Logging → CORS)\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Q: Should Store interface support persistent backend (Redis/etcd)?\n  - A: MemoryStore is current implementation; Store interface allows future extension\n\n- Q: Should AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter informers watch CR status changes?\n  - A: Current implementation uses Pod informers; CR informers can be added via client-go generated informers\n\n- Q: Should GarbageCollector emit metrics for deletion counts/reasons?\n  - A: Not implemented yet; can be added via Prometheus integration\n\n## References\n\n- `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` - Generated client-go for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` - AgentRuntime CRD definition\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` - CodeInterpreter CRD definition\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` - Shared types, labels, annotations, conditions\n- `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response\n- `deployment/client-go.md` - Client-go library documentation"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":37,"character":14},"end":{"line":37,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field WriteTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":13},"end":{"line":38,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":17},"end":{"line":39,"character":17}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDe